Johannesburg mayor Mpho Phalatse and Safety MMC David Tembe spoke with eNCA's Gareth Edwards about the incident. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested a woman who broke into the City of Johannesburg offices on Monday morning. She was found hiding under a desk, in possession of computer hard drives. According to Johannesburg mayor Mpho Phalatse, the same suspect broke into the offices last month. "I was called at about 2am that there was a suspect in the building. She was caught in the act according to our security officers at the Metro Centre," the mayor said. Safety MMC David Tembe said the police are investigating the case, including possible motives.